    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.6.0-dev+522-gac358bfb2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A, vim doesn't support winhighlight\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.8.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\ntest.vim:\r\n```vim\r\nset winhighlight=Normal:Pmenu,CursorLine:PmenuSel\r\ninsert\r\ntext\r\ntext\r\n.\r\nset cursorline\r\nhighlight clear Pmenu\r\nhighlight Pmenu cterm=inverse\r\nhighlight clear PmenuSel\r\n```\r\nThen run:\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean -u test.vim\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe highlight of CursorLine/PmenuSel is red text on default background, so the current line should be highlighted as such.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nInstead it's black text on white background, inverted like Normal/Pmenu is. Inverting Normal seems to have effects beyond just text highlighted as Normal.\r\n\r\nInterestingly, setting cterm=inverse on Normal globally (without winhighlight) has no effect.",
